


     ArpDupLock(31.0)	  ARP Programmers Manual      ArpDupLock(31.0)



     NAME
	  ArpDupLock - Duplicate a lock	and track it.

     SYNOPSIS
	  Lock = ArpDupLock( lock )
	   d0		      d1

     FUNCTION
	  Completely equivalent	to the AmigaDOS	DupLock() function
	  call,	except that the	tracking functions of arp.library are
	  used to keep track of	this allocation	for you.

     INPUTS
	  lock - pointer to a lock

     RESULTS
	  Lock - pointer to a lock or NULL

	  TRACKER - Pointer to the tracker is in A1, or	in LastTracker
		  variable if calling from 'C'.

     REMEMBER
	  You must FreeTrackedItem( TRACKER ) or CloseLibrary()	or
	  ArpExit() to free this lock.

     BUGS
	  None known.

     SEE ALSO
	  DOS DOCUMENTATION, FreeTrackedItem(),	OpenLibrary(),
	  CloseLibrary()

     AUTHOR
	  SDB





















